    "locale": "en",
    "id": "english-learning-professionals",
    "content": "# Professional English Speaking: From Reading to Speaking\n**The 20‑minute daily fix for professionals who need real workplace English.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nYou understand the meeting. You even know the words.\nBut when it’s your turn to speak, you freeze. This playbook fixes that.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nNon‑native professionals who work in global teams and need clear, confident spoken English for:\n- weekly updates\n- client calls\n- cross‑team coordination\n- Q&A under pressure\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (You freeze when speaking)\n- You can read everything, but can’t say it smoothly.\n- Your tone sounds too direct or too weak.\n- You feel slow in real‑time conversations.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **Right‑level challenge (ZPD):** Learn fastest when tasks are just slightly harder than your current level.\n- **Self‑regulated learning (SRL):** Plan, practice, and reflect so each session gets better than the last.\n\nLearn more:\n- ZPD: https://www.simplypsychology.org/Zone-of-Proximal-Development.html\n- SRL: https://lincs.ed.gov/state-resources/federal-initiatives/teal/guide/selfregulated\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Generates realistic workplace scenarios.\n- Roleplays with you and gives corrections.\n- Refines tone, clarity, and structure.\n\n**Human does**\n- Picks the scenario.\n- Speaks out loud.\n- Keeps the final voice and intent.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Pick (3 min)**\nChoose one scenario for today: stand‑up update, status report, conflict resolution, or client call.\n\n**2) Roleplay (12 min)**\nSpeak it out loud. The agent plays the counterpart and fixes grammar, tone, and structure.\n\n**3) Rewrite (5 min)**\nRewrite the same message in a stronger, clearer version. Save it as a reusable template.\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** handle 1 workplace scenario without freezing.\n- **14 days:** speak confidently across 3 scenarios.\n- **30 days:** build a personal “workplace English script library.”\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s roleplay scenario:\n\n```\nYou are my workplace English roleplay partner.\nScenario: weekly team update.\nMy role: project owner.\nYour role: manager.\nGoal: help me deliver a clear 60‑second update, then give direct feedback on clarity, tone, and structure.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Workplace Roleplay Generator: https://skills.sh/search?q=roleplay\n- Tone & Clarity Coach: https://skills.sh/search?q=tone%20coach\n- Daily Feedback Tracker: https://skills.sh/search?q=feedback%20tracker\n- Vocabulary Micro‑deck: https://skills.sh/search?q=vocabulary%20flashcards\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n- ElevenLabs Agents (voice roleplay + pronunciation): https://skills.sh/jackspace/claudeskillz/elevenlabs-agents\n- sag (ElevenLabs TTS for speaking practice): https://skills.sh/moltbot/moltbot/sag\n- ElevenLabs Text-to-Speech: https://skills.sh/elevenlabs/skills/text-to-speech\n- ElevenLabs Speech-to-Text: https://skills.sh/elevenlabs/skills/speech-to-text\n- Speech Generation: https://skills.sh/openai/skills/speech\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nStart tonight with one scenario: your next weekly update.\n\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections.\n"
