    "locale": "en",
    "id": "learning-science-system",
    "content": "# Learning Science‑Driven Study System\n**A simple system built on how learning actually works.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nMost study plans ignore how the brain learns. This playbook doesn’t.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nAnyone who wants a reliable, science‑based learning system that scales.\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (Study doesn’t stick)\n- You study hard but forget quickly.\n- You don’t know why some methods work and others fail.\n- You keep starting over.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **ZPD:** challenge just beyond comfort.\n- **CLT:** reduce cognitive overload.\n- **SRL:** plan, monitor, reflect.\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Adjusts difficulty and pacing.\n- Breaks content into chunks.\n- Prompts reflection and review.\n\n**Human does**\n- Sets goals and priorities.\n- Commits to consistent practice.\n- Decides what matters most.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Plan (3 min)**\nSet one learning goal for today.\n\n**2) Learn (12 min)**\nStudy a chunk sized for your attention and ability.\n\n**3) Reflect (5 min)**\nAnswer: what did I learn, and what still confuses me?\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** clearer learning routine.\n- **14 days:** better retention and confidence.\n- **30 days:** a system you can reuse forever.\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s workflow:\n\n```\nCreate a 20‑minute learning plan for linear regression using small chunks and 2 reflection questions.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Adaptive Study Planner: https://skills.sh/search?q=adaptive%20study\n- Chunking Assistant: https://skills.sh/search?q=chunking\n- Reflection Prompter: https://skills.sh/search?q=reflection\n- Spaced Repetition Builder: https://skills.sh/search?q=spaced%20repetition\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n- Learning Medusa: https://skills.sh/medusajs/medusa-agent-skills/learning-medusa\n- Memory, Retrieval & Learning: https://agent-skills.md/skills/lyndonkl/claude/memory-retrieval-learning\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nStart with one goal today. Don’t chase everything—learn what sticks.\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections.\n"
