    "locale": "en",
    "id": "personal-knowledge-system",
    "content": "# Personal Knowledge System: Stop Losing What You Learn\n**Turn information overload into a simple, usable learning system.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nYou read a lot, save a lot, and still forget most of it. This playbook makes learning stick.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nProfessionals and students who consume lots of information and want a clean system for recall and reuse.\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (Notes don’t compound)\n- Notes are messy and never reused.\n- You don’t know what matters until it’s too late.\n- You can’t find your best ideas when you need them.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **Capture less, connect more.**\n- **Build retrieval, not storage.**\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Captures and tags sources.\n- Summarizes and formats notes.\n- Surfaces weekly review prompts.\n\n**Human does**\n- Decides what matters.\n- Writes the final insight.\n- Builds connections between notes.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Capture (5 min)**\nSave 1–2 meaningful ideas from today’s reading.\n\n**2) Connect (10 min)**\nLink the idea to one existing note or project.\n\n**3) Output (5 min)**\nWrite a short summary you can reuse later.\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** a clean daily capture habit.\n- **14 days:** connected notes you can search and reuse.\n- **30 days:** a working knowledge base you trust.\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s workflow:\n\n```\nFrom today’s reading notes, extract 3 reusable knowledge cards.\nFor each: title, one‑sentence summary, and 2 tags.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Knowledge Capture Bot: https://skills.sh/search?q=note%20capture\n- Smart Summarizer: https://skills.sh/search?q=summarizer\n- Tagging Assistant: https://skills.sh/search?q=tagging\n- Weekly Review Prompt: https://skills.sh/search?q=weekly%20review\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n\n- Reading List Manager: https://skills.sh/eddiebe147/claude-settings/reading-list-manager\n- Summarize (URLs/files/videos): https://skills.sh/moltbot/moltbot/summarize\n- Obsidian Study Vault Builder: https://skills.sh/belumume/claude-skills/obsidian-study-vault-builder\n- Zettelkasten Notes: https://skills.sh/joostbouma/agent-skills/zettelkasten-notes\n\n- Remembering Conversations: https://skills.sh/obra/episodic-memory/remembering-conversations\n- Obsidian Markdown: https://skills.sh/kepano/obsidian-skills/obsidian-markdown\n- Obsidian Bases: https://skills.sh/kepano/obsidian-skills/obsidian-bases\n- JSON Canvas: https://skills.sh/kepano/obsidian-skills/json-canvas\n- Excalidraw Diagram: https://skills.sh/axtonliu/axton-obsidian-visual-skills/excalidraw-diagram\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nSave one idea today, then connect it to one thing you’re already working on.\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections."
