    "locale": "en",
    "id": "research-paper-reading",
    "content": "# Research Paper Reading & Synthesis\n**Stop skimming. Start extracting what actually matters.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nYou read papers, but nothing sticks. This playbook gives you a repeatable way to extract value.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nResearchers, students, and professionals who need to keep up with technical literature.\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (Too much to read)\n- Papers are dense and time‑consuming.\n- You forget what you read a week later.\n- You can’t tell which papers are worth deep reading.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **Skim smart, then go deep.**\n- **Summaries are useless unless they drive decisions.**\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Extracts abstract, methods, and results.\n- Generates a one‑page summary.\n- Flags claims and evidence.\n\n**Human does**\n- Decides if it’s worth deep reading.\n- Interprets implications.\n- Connects the paper to real projects.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Triage (3 min)**\nDecide if the paper is relevant.\n\n**2) Extract (12 min)**\nThe agent summarizes methods, key results, and limitations.\n\n**3) Synthesize (5 min)**\nWrite one takeaway that changes your thinking.\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** a reliable triage habit.\n- **14 days:** 5 paper summaries you can trust.\n- **30 days:** clear research direction based on evidence.\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s workflow:\n\n```\nSummarize this paper into one page: key question, method, results, and 2 limitations.\nThen state whether it’s worth deep reading and why.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Paper Summarizer: https://skills.sh/search?q=paper%20summarizer\n- Evidence Extractor: https://skills.sh/search?q=evidence%20extractor\n- Claim Checker: https://skills.sh/search?q=claim%20verification\n- Literature Tracker: https://skills.sh/search?q=literature%20tracker\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n- Academic Research Writer: https://skills.sh/endigo/claude-skills/academic-research-writer\n- Reading List Manager: https://skills.sh/eddiebe147/claude-settings/reading-list-manager\n- Summarize (URLs/files/videos): https://skills.sh/moltbot/moltbot/summarize\n- Research Workflow: https://skills.sh/jwynia/agent-skills/research-workflow\n- Academic Writing Standards: https://skills.sh/seabbs/claude-code-config/academic-writing-standards\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nPick one paper today. Decide in 3 minutes if it’s worth your time.\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections.\n"
