    "locale": "en",
    "id": "technical-interview-training",
    "content": "# Technical Interview Training: Practice Like It’s Real\n**Short, sharp simulations that build real interview confidence.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nYou can solve problems alone, but interviews feel different. This playbook makes practice realistic.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nCandidates preparing for technical interviews in software, data, or product roles.\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (Pressure breaks performance)\n- You blank out under time pressure.\n- You don’t know how to explain your thinking.\n- Practice doesn’t feel realistic.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **Simulate the real environment.**\n- **Explain out loud to improve clarity and speed.**\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Generates interview‑style questions.\n- Times you and gives feedback.\n- Evaluates explanation quality.\n\n**Human does**\n- Solves and explains out loud.\n- Reflects on mistakes.\n- Refines approach.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Question (3 min)**\nPick one question at the right difficulty level.\n\n**2) Solve (12 min)**\nSolve it while speaking your reasoning out loud.\n\n**3) Review (5 min)**\nFix the one biggest mistake and write a better explanation.\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** faster reasoning under time pressure.\n- **14 days:** clearer explanations.\n- **30 days:** stable interview performance.\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s workflow:\n\n```\nGive me one medium‑level coding interview question.\nI will explain my solution; then score clarity (1‑5) and list 2 improvements.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Interview Question Generator: https://skills.sh/search?q=interview%20questions\n- Timer & Feedback Coach: https://skills.sh/search?q=interview%20feedback\n- Explanation Checker: https://skills.sh/search?q=explanation%20coach\n- Difficulty Adjuster: https://skills.sh/search?q=adaptive%20practice\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n- LeetCode Teacher: https://skills.sh/jamesrochabrun/skills/leetcode-teacher\n- None yet. Add once a real downloadable skill is confirmed.\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nPick one question tonight and explain every step out loud.\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections.\n"
