    "locale": "en",
    "id": "writing-for-impact",
    "content": "# Writing for Professional Impact\n**Make your writing clear, persuasive, and hard to ignore.**\n\n---\n\n## Quick Start\nYou write all day, but your message still gets lost. This playbook fixes the structure.\n\n---\n\n## Who It’s For\nProfessionals who need to write for decisions, influence, or clear action.\n\n---\n\n## The Pain (Message gets lost)\n- Your writing feels long but not strong.\n- People misunderstand your point.\n- You spend too long editing.\n\n---\n\n## The Simple Learning Logic\n- **Structure beats style.**\n- **Clarity drives action.**\n\n---\n\n## The Human‑Agent Split\n**Agent does**\n- Proposes a clear outline.\n- Flags ambiguity and fluff.\n- Suggests stronger phrasing.\n\n**Human does**\n- Defines the intent and audience.\n- Chooses the final tone.\n- Approves the final argument.\n\n---\n\n## The 3‑Step Routine (20 min/day)\n**1) Frame (3 min)**\nDefine your goal and the decision you want.\n\n**2) Outline (12 min)**\nThe agent generates a tight structure and edits for clarity.\n\n**3) Finalize (5 min)**\nRewrite the core message in one strong paragraph.\n\n---\n\n## Expected Outcomes (Time‑boxed)\n- **7 days:** shorter, clearer writing.\n- **14 days:** stronger responses and faster approvals.\n- **30 days:** a personal writing system you trust.\n\n---\n\n## Starter Prompt (Example, Unverified)\nUse this once to generate today’s workflow:\n\n```\nCreate a 5‑sentence executive summary for this decision: \nWe need to prioritize latency fixes over new features for Q2.\n```\n\n---\n\n## Skill Pack\n\n**Candidate Skills (not yet verified)**\n- Clarity Editor: https://skills.sh/search?q=clarity%20editor\n- Argument Builder: https://skills.sh/search?q=argument%20builder\n- Tone Adjuster: https://skills.sh/search?q=tone%20rewrite\n- Executive Summary Generator: https://skills.sh/search?q=executive%20summary\n\n**Verified Skills (downloadable)**\n\n\n- Technical Writer: https://skills.sh/shubhamsaboo/awesome-llm-apps/technical-writer\n- Documentation Writing: https://skills.sh/nilecui/skillsbase/documentation-writing\n- Writing Clearly and Concisely: https://skills.sh/softaworks/agent-toolkit/writing-clearly-and-concisely\n- Doc Co‑Authoring: https://skills.sh/anthropics/skills/doc-coauthoring\n- Academic Writing Standards: https://skills.sh/seabbs/claude-code-config/academic-writing-standards\n\n- Copywriting: https://skills.sh/coreyhaines31/marketingskills/copywriting\n- Writing Plans: https://skills.sh/obra/superpowers/writing-plans\n\n- Writing Skills: https://skills.sh/obra/superpowers/writing-skills\n- Email Best Practices: https://skills.sh/resend/email-best-practices/email-best-practices\n\n---\n\n## Evidence & Verification\n- **UNTESTED**: Not yet validated by humans\n- **TESTED**: 2+ users × 3 days\n- **VERIFIED**: 10+ users × 7 days\n\n**Current status:** UNTESTED\n\nIf you test this, report your results and we’ll upgrade the status.\n\n---\n\n## Call to Action\nWrite one paragraph today as if a decision depends on it.\n---\n\n## Open‑Source Community\nThis playbook is community‑maintained. If you improve it, share your changes so others benefit.\n\n**Contribute**\n- Improve clarity or add better scenarios\n- Add a real downloadable skill (link + repo)\n- Report test results (what you tried, for how long, and the outcome)\n\n\n\n---\n\n## Change Log\n- 2026‑02‑07 (UTC): Added open‑source contribution sections."
